dataIdInfo.idPurp: GLEAM ecosystem services, aggregated into 2km grid cells, for use by Lucas Gloege in a Lake Michigan research project.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Six of the GLEAM ecosystem services were aggregated to a 2km grid covering Lake Michigan. Each point service location (beaches, birding hotspots, boat launches, marinas and municipal water intake pipes) and corresponding measure of service delivery (beach visits, birding hotspot visits, boat launch parking spaces, marina slips, and municipal water withdrawals) were aggregated using the Spatial Join tool in ArcGIS. Parks, which are represented by polygons, were assigned to each 2km cell in which they reside, and an area-weighted measure of visitation was calculated.

For a more detailed description of how individual services were mapped, please see:

Allan et al. 2015. Using cultural ecosysem services to inform restoration priorities in the Laurentian Great Lakes. Frontiers in Ecology and the Environment.. 13(8): 418-424. DOI: 10.1890/140328
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Great Lakes Environmental Assessment and Mapping Project, University of Michigan
